  "name": "Prostate Cancer - Comprehensive Provider Query (DX + Meds + Labs + Procedures)",
  "description": "Simulates a urologist/medical oncologist identifying their complete prostate cancer patient population. Combines: PCa diagnosis codes, ADT/anti-androgens, elevated PSA, and biopsy procedures. **Second 4-resource-type union test in the suite** (after CRC).",
  "prompt": "I need to identify my complete prostate cancer patient population for a quality improvement initiative on ADT adherence and PSA surveillance. From clinical experience, PCa patients are documented in different ways: most have a formal prostate cancer diagnosis (often stage-specific), most are on ADT or anti-androgens (leuprolide, bicalutamide, enzalutamide, abiraterone, degarelix), most have undergone biopsy, and many have elevated PSA.\n\nPlease run multiple FHIR queries to capture the full population:\n1. Patients with any prostate cancer diagnosis\n2. Patients prescribed ADT/anti-androgens (leuprolide, bicalutamide, enzalutamide, abiraterone, degarelix)\n3. Patients who have undergone prostate biopsy\n4. Patients with elevated PSA (>4 ng/mL)\n\nFor each query, return the matching resources. I want the union of all patients found. Note: this is a male-only population.",
  "metadata": {
    "implementation_guide": "US Core 5.0.0",
    "multi_query": true,
    "algorithm_path": "comprehensive",
    "algorithm_path_description": "Union of PCa dx + ADT Rx + biopsy Procedure + elevated PSA. **Second 4-resource-type union test** in the suite.",
